events.name: 3rd Singapore Inorganic Chemistry Symposium (SICS 2017)
events.description: About the symposium:The Singapore Inorganic Chemistry Symposium is an annual joint NUS-NTU day symposium that provides a platform for young inorganic chemists to present their research. The symposium is broadly based around all inorganic chemical study, covering areas such as bioinorganic, metal catalysis, inorganic materials andcoordination chemistry.This year, the symposium will be hosted by NUS, and will feature short oral presentations and poster presentations by young researchers. To expose young Singapore based chemists to worldleading research, invited lectures will also be provided by Professor Simon Aldridge from the University of Oxford, and Professor JJ Vittal from the National University of Singapore.
events.location: University Hall, Auditorium Level 2, National University of Singapore, Lee Kong Chian Wing, 21 Lower Kent Ridge Road, Singapore 119077
events.group_name: NUS Department of Chemistry and NTU Division of Chemistry and Biochemistry
